| width = 33%
}}
On 10 September 2016, De Bruyne scored and assisted in the first [[Manchester derby]] of the [[2016–17 Premier League|season]] which City won 2–1 and was awarded the ''Man of the Match''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37263921|title=Manchester United 1–2 Manchester City|date=10 September 2016|work=BBC Sport|access-date=27 December 2019|archive-date=21 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321081208/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37263921|url-status=live}}</ref> On 17 September, De Bruyne was awarded the ''Man of the Match'', in a 4–0 win over Bournemouth. De Bruyne scored the first, assisted the fourth, and provided key passes on both the second and third goals.<ref>{{cite web|title=Manchester City v Bournemouth Premier League match report|url=http://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/2016/09/17/city-v-bournemouth-16-september/1474036032274|website=Manchester City|date=17 September 2017|access-date=18 September 2016|archive-date=18 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918234021/http://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/2016/09/17/city-v-bournemouth-16-september/1474036032274|url-status=dead}}</ref> After the international break, Manchester City drew their next game, against Everton, played on 15 October with the scoreline finishing at 1–1. Agüero and De Bruyne both missed their penalties while [[Nolito]] came off the bench to equalise for City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37594239|title=Manchester City 1–1 Everton|date=15 October 2016|work=BBC Sport|access-date=19 December 2017|archive-date=1 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501222458/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37594239|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 1 November 2016, De Bruyne scored from a [[Direct free kick|free-kick]] in the club's 3–1 win over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/11/01/manchester-city-vs-barcelona-live-score-and-goal-updates-from-ch/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/11/01/manchester-city-vs-barcelona-live-score-and-goal-updates-from-ch/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=Manchester City 3 Barcelona 1: Pep Guardiola masterminds City comeback as Gundogan grabs double|first1=Sam|last1=Wallace|first2=J. J.|last2=Bull|date=1 November 2016|work=The Telegraph|access-date=19 December 2017}}{{cbignore}}</ref> On 21 January 2017, De Bruyne was involved in both of City's goals, as he netted once himself and also assisted [[Leroy Sané]]'s, in a 2–2 home draw with [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]; he was subsequently named man of the match.<ref>{{Cite news|last=McNulty|first=Phil|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38620041|title=Manchester City 2–2 Tottenham Hotspur|date=12 January 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=19 December 2017|archive-date=20 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190320222815/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38620041|url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 March, De Bruyne displayed an excellent performance in a 1–1 draw against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at the [[City of Manchester Stadium|Etihad Stadium]], where he set up a goal for Agüero.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39246699|title=Manchester City 1–1 Liverpool|date=19 March 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=19 December 2017|archive-date=23 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170523090655/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39246699|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2017–18 season====
[[File:Kevin de Bruyne (36243870980).jpg|thumb|De Bruyne during a pre-season training session in 2017]]

De Bruyne set up both Agüero's and [[Gabriel Jesus]]' goals, on 9 September 2017, in a 5–0 home victory over [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Yew|first=Oliver|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/man-city-vs-liverpool/373132|title=Manchester City 5–0 Liverpool: Jurgen Klopp's side suffer after Sadio Mane's red card|date=9 September 2017|access-date=19 December 2017|work=Sky Sports|archive-date=17 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171217043135/http://www.skysports.com/football/man-city-vs-liverpool/373132|url-status=live}}</ref> On 16 September, De Bruyne assisted Agüero for his first goal in an eventual 6–0 win over [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22390|title=Watford v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=16 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016134855/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22390|url-status=live}}</ref> On 26 September, De Bruyne scored his first goal of the [[2017–18 Manchester City F.C. season|2017–18 season]] in a 2–0 win over [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41378842|title=Manchester City 2–0 Shakhtar Donetsk|date=26 September 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401032250/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41378842|url-status=live}}</ref> On 30 September, he scored his first goal of the [[2017–18 Premier League]] season, as City beat his former club [[Chelsea FC|Chelsea]] with a 1–0 scoreline at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]].<ref>{{cite news|last=McNulty|first=Phil|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41370356|title=Chelsea 0–1 Manchester City|date=30 September 2017|access-date=19 December 2017|work=BBC Sport|archive-date=22 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222172749/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41370356|url-status=live}}</ref> On 14 October, De Bruyne provided two assists in a 7–2 win over [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22417|title=Man City v Stoke, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=15 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215182801/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22417|url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 November, De Bruyne scored in a 3–1 win over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22445|title=Man City v Arsenal, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401173915/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22445|url-status=live}}</ref> On 18 November, he scored in a 2–0 away win over [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22457|title=Leicester v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401093125/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22457|url-status=live}}</ref> On 29 November, he scored City's opener and assisted [[Raheem Sterling]]'s last-minute winner in a 2–1 win over [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22480|title=Man City v Southampton, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401042748/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22480|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 13 December 2017, De Bruyne scored in a 4–0 away win over [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]], which extended their record run of consecutive top-flight wins to 15 games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22506|title=Swansea v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=15 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215184306/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22506|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42247112|title=Swansea City 0–4 Manchester City|date=13 December 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=10 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210063328/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42247112|url-status=live}}</ref> On 16 December, he scored in a 4–1 win over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], with [[Pep Guardiola]] saying that De Bruyne is "helping the club become a better institution".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22518|title=Man City v Spurs, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401042723/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22518|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42290590|title=Manchester City 4–1 Tottenham Hotspur|date=16 December 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=2 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002556/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42290590|url-status=live}}</ref> On 27 December, De Bruyne provided an assist for Sterling's goal in a 1–0 win over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22538|title=Newcastle v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401045806/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22538|url-status=live}}</ref> On 9 January, De Bruyne scored in a 2–1 win over Bristol City in the [[2017–18 EFL Cup#Semi-finals|first leg of the semi-finals]] of the [[2017–18 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42537815|title=Manchester City 2–1 Bristol City|year=2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=2 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402011123/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42537815|url-status=live}}</ref> On 20 January, he provided an assist for Agüero's first goal of the game (who scored a [[hat-trick]] in the game), in a 3–1 win over Newcastle United.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22577|title=Man City v Newcastle, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401042739/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22577|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42672232|title=Manchester City 3–1 Newcastle United|year=2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=18 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718024303/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42672232|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Manchester United v Manchester City, 10 December 2017 (20).jpg|left|thumb|De Bruyne during the [[Manchester derby]] at [[Old Trafford]], on 10 December 2017, which City won 2–1]]

On 22 January 2018, De Bruyne signed a new long-term contract with the club, keeping him at the club until 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/january/de-bruyne-pens-new-five-year-contract|title=Kevin De Bruyne Pens New Five-Year Contract|date=22 January 2018|access-date=22 January 2018|website=mancity.co.uk|publisher=Manchester City|archive-date=15 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215182806/https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/january/de-bruyne-pens-new-five-year-contract|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="BBC Sport">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42698924|title=Bristol City 2–3 Manchester City (Agg: 3–5)|year=2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=5 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605164222/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42698924|url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 January, he scored the winning goal in a 3–2 win over Bristol City in the [[2017–18 EFL Cup#Semi-finals|EFL Cup semi-final second leg]], which helped City advance to the [[2018 EFL Cup Final|final]], having won the tie by an aggregate scoreline of 5–3.<ref name="BBC Sport"/> On 31 January, he scored and assisted in a 3–0 win over [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]], and was voted [[BBC Sport|BBC]] ''Man of the Match''.<ref name="BBC Sport"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42799045|title=Manchester City 3–0 West Bromwich Albion|year=2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001081826/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42799045|url-status=live}}</ref> On 10 February, he provided three assists, two for Agüero and one for Raheem Sterling, in a 5–1 win over [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], taking his assists tally to 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22605|title=Man City v Leicester, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401045809/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22605|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42927832|title=Manchester City 5–1 Leicester City|date=10 February 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=3 February 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203045717/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42927832|url-status=live}}</ref> On 25 February, he started in the [[2018 EFL Cup Final]] against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], and played the whole 90 minutes, with Manchester City winning 3–0 to obtain their first piece of silverware of the [[2017–18 Manchester City F.C. season|2017–18 season]], and their first trophy overall under Pep Guardiola.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43101681|title=Arsenal 0–3 Manchester City|date=25 February 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401043826/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43101681|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 31 March 2018, he provided an assist for Gabriel Jesus in a 3–1 win over [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], ensuring that City would require only one more win to secure the [[2017–18 Premier League|Premier League title]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22656|title=Everton v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401042752/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22656|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43524315|title=Everton 1–3 Manchester City|date=31 March 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=17 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190817140701/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43524315|url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 April, he scored in a 5–0 win over Swansea City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22688|title=Man City v Swansea, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=7 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207212847/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22688|url-status=live}}</ref> On 13 May, on the final day of the season, De Bruyne assisted Gabriel Jesus' winning goal in a 1–0 win over [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], which took champions City's total points tally to 100. De Bruyne was also voted as [[BBC Sport|BBC]] ''Man of the Match''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/22718|title=Southampton v Man City, 2017/18 {{!}} Premier League|publisher=Premier League|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401042745/https://www.premierleague.com/match/22718|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44020180|title=Southampton 0–1 Manchester City|date=13 May 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=30 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830091122/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44020180|url-status=live}}</ref> For his 16 assists registered across the league season, De Bruyne won the inaugural [[Premier League Playmaker of the Season]] award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/690283|title=De Bruyne edges Playmaker award|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514011726/https://www.premierleague.com/news/690283|url-status=live}}</ref> He was also selected in the [[PFA Team of the Year (2010s)#Premier League 9|PFA Team of the Year]], and was also voted as [[Manchester City F.C.#Player of the Year|Manchester City Player of the Season]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43810017|title=Manchester City players dominate PFA team of the year|date=18 April 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=30 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211230211922/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43810017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/may/kevin-de-bruyne-man-city-etihad-player-of-the-season|title=Etihad Player of the Season {{!}} Kevin De Bruyne|work=mancity.com|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=15 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215182904/https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/may/kevin-de-bruyne-man-city-etihad-player-of-the-season|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thepfa.com/thepfa/pfaawards/pfa-premier-league-of-the-year-2018|title=The PFA Premier League Team of the Year|last=ThePFA.com|website=thepfa.com|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422123603/https://www.thepfa.com/thepfa/pfaawards/pfa-premier-league-of-the-year-2018|archive-date=22 April 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>

====2018–19 season====
On 15 August 2018, De Bruyne suffered a knee injury during a training session, with several news websites reporting that he could potentially not play for up to three months.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45200783|title=Kevin de Bruyne: Man City midfielder suffers knee injury in training|date=15 August 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=17 August 2018|archive-date=20 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420193347/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45200783|url-status=live}}</ref> Two days later, Manchester City confirmed that he had suffered a lesion of the [[Fibular collateral ligament|lateral collateral ligament]] in his right knee, with no surgery required, and that he was expected to not play for three months.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/august/kevin-de-bruyne-injury-update-latest-manchester-city|title=Kevin De Bruyne injury update|website=mancity.com|access-date=17 August 2018|archive-date=15 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215182929/https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/august/kevin-de-bruyne-injury-update-latest-manchester-city|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45222678|title=Kevin de Bruyne: Manchester City midfielder out for three months|date=17 August 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=17 August 2018|archive-date=5 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190505041707/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45222678|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/11474713/manchester-citys-kevin-de-bruyne-out-for-three-months-with-knee-injury|title=Manchester City's Kevin De Bruyne out for three months with knee injury|work=Sky Sports|access-date=17 August 2018|archive-date=6 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200106075949/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/11474713/manchester-citys-kevin-de-bruyne-out-for-three-months-with-knee-injury|url-status=live}}</ref> Soon after De Bruyne returned to action in October 2018, he once again suffered a knee ligament injury in the fourth round of the [[EFL Cup]] against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. The injury was expected to keep him out for 5–6 weeks<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/november/kevin-de-bruyne-injury-news-man-city-latest-update|title=Kevin De Bruyne suffers ligament damage|website=mancity.com|access-date=20 November 2018|archive-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305002641/https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2018/november/kevin-de-bruyne-injury-news-man-city-latest-update|url-status=live}}</ref> but he resumed full training much earlier than expected after only 3 weeks out.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/nov/12/kevin-de-bruyne-manchester-city-back-early-injury|title=Kevin De Bruyne set to be back for Manchester City earlier than expected|last=Jackson|first=Jamie|date=12 November 2018|work=The Guardian|access-date=20 November 2018|archive-date=9 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200109171336/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/nov/12/kevin-de-bruyne-manchester-city-back-early-injury|url-status=live}}</ref> He came on as substitute in the [[2019 FA Cup Final|FA Cup final]] against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]], scoring the third goal and assisting two more, as City won the first-ever domestic treble in English men's football.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/may/18/manchester-city-win-treble-watford-fa-cup-final-match-report|title=Manchester City win FA Cup to seal treble with 6–0 demolition of Watford|last=Wembley|first=Daniel Taylor at|date=18 May 2019|work=The Observer|access-date=18 May 2019|issn=0029-7712|archive-date=1 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301211541/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/may/18/manchester-city-win-treble-watford-fa-cup-final-match-report|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48236232|title=Man City 6–0 Watford: Raheem Sterling scores FA Cup final hat-trick|date=18 May 2019|access-date=18 May 2019|archive-date=31 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531022822/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48236232|url-status=live}}</ref> His performances meant he was named ''Man of the Match''.<ref name=":0" />

====2019–20 season====
On 30 November 2019, De Bruyne scored a half-volley in a 2–2 draw against Newcastle in the league, that strike was later voted as [[Premier League Goal of the Month]] for November.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Shelvey stunner holds Man City|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50526605|access-date=5 March 2021|archive-date=24 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124004100/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50526605|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Edwards|first=John|title=De Bruyne strike scoops Goal of the Month|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/first-team-news/2019/december/kevin-de-bruyne-wins-premier-league-goal-of-the-month|access-date=5 March 2021|website=mancity.com}}</ref> On 15 December, he scored a brace in a 3–0 [[2019–20 Premier League|Premier League]] win over Arsenal at the Emirates.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50702875|title=Manchester City pushed Arsenal deeper into crisis as they won with embarrassing ease at Emirates Stadium.|publisher=BBC|date=15 December 2019|access-date=26 February 2020|archive-date=30 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230011815/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50702875|url-status=live}}</ref>

De Bruyne scored his 50th City goal in all competitions on 26 February 2020 in their 2–1 victory, coming from behind, over [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in their Champions League [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League#Round of 16|Round of 16]] clash.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sport.bt.com/news/manchester-city-fight-back-to-beat-real-madrid-at-bernabeu-S11364433721545|title=Manchester City fight back to beat Real Madrid at Bernabeu|website=BT Sport|date=26 February 2020|access-date=26 February 2020|archive-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227000841/https://sport.bt.com/news/manchester-city-fight-back-to-beat-real-madrid-at-bernabeu-S11364433721545|url-status=live}}</ref>

In the final Premier League match of the season, City beat [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] 5–0 at home. De Bruyne scored two goals and registered his 20th league assist, which equalled [[Thierry Henry]]'s record for the most assists in a season, and also won his second [[Premier League Playmaker of the Season|Playmaker of the Season]] award.<ref name=":1">{{cite web|date=26 July 2020|title=Kevin de Bruyne: Twentieth assist of season equals Thierry Henry's record|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53545450|access-date=26 July 2020|work=BBC Sport|archive-date=27 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727001119/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53545450|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/manchester-city/story/4146843/man-city-kevin-de-bruyne-premier-league-assist-record-thierry-henry|title=Man City's De Bruyne equals Premier League assist record for single season|publisher=ESPN|date=26 July 2020|access-date=27 July 2020|archive-date=27 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727072103/https://www.espn.com/soccer/manchester-city/story/4146843/man-city-kevin-de-bruyne-premier-league-assist-record-thierry-henry|url-status=live}}</ref> In addition he became the first player in history to reach 20 assists in a single season in two of [[Big Five (association football)|Europe's top five leagues]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/two-assists-taken-away-de-bruyne-premier-league-share-record/2vikmfoncye185ixnubn94i4|title='You took two away from me!' – De Bruyne happy to share Premier League assists record with Henry|website=Goal (website)|date=26 July 2020|access-date=27 July 2020|archive-date=28 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200728120503/https://www.goal.com/en/news/two-assists-taken-away-de-bruyne-premier-league-share-record/2vikmfoncye185ixnubn94i4|url-status=live}}</ref> His long range curler in that game also won him [[Premier League Goal of the Month]] for the second time in the season.<ref>{{cite web|title=De Bruyne completes double with Budweiser Goal of the Month|date=3 August 2020 |url=http://www.premierleague.com/news/1747213|access-date=5 March 2021|publisher=Premier League|archive-date=9 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809173603/https://www.premierleague.com/news/1747213|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the end of the season he was awarded the [[Premier League Player of the Season]] after scoring 13 goals, providing 20 assists and creating 104 chances from open play, the most for a player in any of Europe's top five leagues since 2006.<ref>{{Cite news |date=16 August 2020 |title=Kevin de Bruyne: Manchester City midfielder named Premier League player of season |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53797353 |access-date=16 August 2020 |archive-date=27 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927021728/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53797353/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|user=OptaJoe |number=1294934100265050112 |date=16 August 2020 |title=104 – Kevin De Bruyne created 104 chances in open play in the Premier League in 2019–20, the most for a player in any of Europe's top five leagues since this data is available for each competition (2006-07+). Worthy.}}</ref>

He was also named in the [[PFA Team of the Year (2010s)|PFA Team of the Year]] and won the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year|PFA Player of the Year]] award, becoming the first ever Manchester City player to win it.<ref name=":2">{{cite web|title=Man City midfielder De Bruyne beats Liverpool stars to PFA Player of the Year award {{!}} Goal.com|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/man-city-midfielder-de-bruyne-beats-liverpool-stars-to-pfa/g0h1skp0eo0a1l1vxx8u5f6qf|access-date=8 September 2020|website=Goal (website)|archive-date=27 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927021733/https://www.goal.com/en/news/man-city-midfielder-de-bruyne-beats-liverpool-stars-to-pfa/g0h1skp0eo0a1l1vxx8u5f6qf/|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2020–21 season====
[[File:2021-12-07 Fußball, Männer, UEFA Champions League, RB Leipzig - Manchester City FC 1DX 2723 by Stepro (cropped).jpg|thumb|De Bruyne on the ball for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the Champions League against [[RB Leipzig]] in 2021]]
On 21 September 2020, De Bruyne scored and assisted in a 3–1 away win over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in City's first game of the season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Man City hold off Wolves fightback to claim victory|date=18 September 2020 |url=http://www.premierleague.com/news/1834283|access-date=21 September 2020|publisher=Premier League|archive-date=27 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927021742/https://www.premierleague.com/news/1834283/|url-status=live}}</ref> With the crucial visit of the Premier League champions, Liverpool, De Bruyne assisted Gabriel Jesus' equaliser before winning a penalty, which he subsequently fired wide. The game ended in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite news|title=De Bruyne misses penalty in draw|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54766716|access-date=24 November 2020|archive-date=27 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227080825/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54766716|url-status=live}}</ref> On 7 April, De Bruyne signed a four-year contract,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56659261 |title=Kevin de Bruyne: Man City midfielder signs new deal that runs until 2025 |website=BBC Sport |date=7 April 2021 |access-date=7 April 2021 |archive-date=14 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210614202841/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56659261 |url-status=live }}</ref> after negotiating it with help of statistical data to make case for a 30% pay increase.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Glendenning |first=Barry |date=24 May 2021 |title=Premier League 2020-21 review: players of the season |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/may/24/premier-league-2020-21-review-players-of-the-season |access-date=29 March 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

On 25 April 2021, De Bruyne's free-kick was headed into the goal by [[Aymeric Laporte]], allowing City to win 1–0 against Tottenham Hotspur in the [[2021 EFL Cup Final|EFL Cup Final]] at [[Wembley Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56790307 |title=Manchester City 1–0 Tottenham Hotspur |website=BBC Sport |date=25 April 2021 |access-date=25 April 2021 |archive-date=29 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210429085606/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56790307 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 28 April, he scored a goal in a 2–1 away win over Paris Saint-Germain in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56880443 |title=Paris Saint Germain 1–2 Manchester City |website=BBC Sport |date=28 April 2021 |access-date=28 April 2021 |archive-date=3 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503084542/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56880443 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 29 May, De Bruyne had a head injury after colliding with [[Antonio Rüdiger]] in the second half of the [[2021 UEFA Champions League Final|Champions League Final]], to be substituted by Gabriel Jesus; however, his team lost 1–0 against his former club Chelsea.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4211224/2021/05/29/kevin-de-bruyne-suffers-head-injury-in-champions-league-final/ |title=Kevin de Bruyne suffers head injury in Champions League final |website=The Athletic |date=29 May 2021 |access-date=30 May 2021 |archive-date=2 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602215140/https://theathletic.com/news/kevin-de-bruyne-injury-man-city-chelsea-champions-league-final/TXqts3Ex1HLF |url-status=live }}</ref> Medical scans after the game revealed De Bruyne to have suffered [[Nasal fracture|acute nose bone]] and [[Orbit (anatomy)|left orbital]] fractures, placing doubt on his participation in the rescheduled [[UEFA Euro 2020]] tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://soccer.nbcsports.com/2021/05/30/de-bruyne-injury-news-update-latest/|title=Kevin de Bruyne injury update|first=Joe|last=Prince-Wright|work=[[NBC Sports]]|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=30 May 2021|access-date=30 May 2021|archive-date=31 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210531120748/https://soccer.nbcsports.com/2021/05/30/de-bruyne-injury-news-update-latest/|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the end of the season, De Bruyne was awarded with the PFA Player's Player of the Year award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57376601|title=De Bruyne wins second PFA men's award|work=BBC Sport|access-date=6 June 2021|archive-date=7 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210607161041/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57376601|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2021–22 season====
On 26 April 2022, De Bruyne scored the fastest [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] semi-final goal after 93 seconds in a 4–3 win over Real Madrid in the first leg.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/watch-de-bruyne-scores-fastest-ever-champions-league-semi-final-goal-as-man-city-get-off-to-perfect-start-against-real-madrid/bltd5429f1c8755aea7 |title=Watch: De Bruyne scores fastest-ever Champions League semi-final goal as Man City get off to perfect start against Real Madrid |work=Goal (website) |date=26 April 2023 |access-date=18 July 2023 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718181737/https://www.goal.com/en/news/watch-de-bruyne-scores-fastest-ever-champions-league-semi-final-goal-as-man-city-get-off-to-perfect-start-against-real-madrid/bltd5429f1c8755aea7 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 11 May, he scored four goals inside 24 minutes in City's 5–1 win at Wolverhampton Wanderers, his first hat-trick with the club and the third-quickest in Premier League history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61055884 |title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 1–5 Manchester City |website=BBC Sport |date=11 May 2022 |access-date=12 May 2022 |archive-date=12 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512051556/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61055884 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/de-bruyne-nets-third-fastest-hat-trick-premier-league/blte4802347df032c3e |title=De Bruyne copies Haaland's meditation celebration as four-goal Man City hero appears to welcome summer signing |website=Goal (website) |date=11 May 2022 |access-date=12 May 2022 |archive-date=12 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512155123/https://www.goal.com/en/news/de-bruyne-nets-third-fastest-hat-trick-premier-league/blte4802347df032c3e |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Sky Sports]] commentator [[Andy Hinchcliffe]] described the feat as "Twenty-three minutes of footballing genius" and Jeremy Wilson, writing in ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', said "De Bruyne's 'wrong-footed' hat-trick was one of the best displays in Premier League history".<ref>{{cite web |author=Jeremy Wilson |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2022/05/11/kevin-de-bruyne-genius-wrong-footed-hat-trick/ |title=Why Kevin De Bruyne's 'wrong-footed' hat-trick was one of the best displays in Premier League history |website=The Daily Telegraph |date=12 May 2022 |access-date=12 May 2022 |archive-date=12 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512161427/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2022/05/11/kevin-de-bruyne-genius-wrong-footed-hat-trick/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

De Bruyne was again bestowed with the [[Premier League Player of the Season]] award, becoming the fourth player to win the award more than once.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12618147/kevin-de-bruyne-man-city-playmaker-pips-mohamed-salah-to-win-premier-league-player-of-the-year-award|title=Kevin De Bruyne: Man City playmaker pips Mohamed Salah to win Premier League Player of the Year award|date=21 May 2022|website=skysports.com|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|access-date=28 June 2022|archive-date=28 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220628225525/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12618147/kevin-de-bruyne-man-city-playmaker-pips-mohamed-salah-to-win-premier-league-player-of-the-year-award|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/2621844|title=De Bruyne voted EA SPORTS Player of the Season|date=22 May 2022|publisher=Premier League|access-date=28 June 2022|archive-date=4 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220604175747/https://www.premierleague.com/news/2621844|url-status=live}}</ref> He also went on to win Manchester City's Player of the Year award for the fourth time. As a result, he tied [[Richard Dunne]] for the most player of the year awards at the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/kevin-de-bruyne-voted-manchester-city-s-etihad-player-of-the-season-63788651|title=DE BRUYNE VOTED MANCHESTER CITY'S ETIHAD PLAYER OF THE SEASON|author=Clayton, David|date=22 May 2022|website=mancity.com|publisher=[[Manchester City F.C.]]}}{{Dead link|date=September 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref> In addition, he ended the season as the club's top scorer in the Premier League with 15 goals, which was also his personal best record.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3316370/2022/05/26/how-de-bruyne-turned-from-provider-to-goalscorer-to-lead-manchester-city-to-the-premier-league-title/ |title=How De Bruyne turned from provider to goalscorer to lead Manchester City to the Premier League title |publisher=The Athletic |date=26 May 2022 |access-date=18 July 2023 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718173447/https://theathletic.com/3316370/2022/05/26/how-de-bruyne-turned-from-provider-to-goalscorer-to-lead-manchester-city-to-the-premier-league-title/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2022–23 season====
On 26 April 2023, De Bruyne scored a brace and provided an assist in a 4–1 win over Arsenal, which reduced their rival's lead at the league table to two points, with his team had two games in hand.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/manchester-city-arsenal-premier-league-live-score-updates-result/gSSAeDyINcUm/ |title=How Manchester City dominated Arsenal 4–1 in crucial Premier League title race showdown |publisher=The Athletic |date=26 April 2023 |access-date=18 July 2023 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718181737/https://theathletic.com/live-blogs/manchester-city-arsenal-premier-league-live-score-updates-result/gSSAeDyINcUm/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 9 May, he scored the equaliser for his club in a 1–1 away draw against Real Madrid in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] semi-finals first leg,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/watch-man-city-star-kevin-de-bruyne-hammers-champions-league-semi-final-first-leg-equaliser-against-real-madrid/blt77246db5e800823b |title=WATCH: Man City star Kevin De Bruyne hammers Champions League semi-final first leg equaliser against Real Madrid |work=Goal (website) |date=9 May 2023 |access-date=18 July 2023 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718173447/https://www.goal.com/en/news/watch-man-city-star-kevin-de-bruyne-hammers-champions-league-semi-final-first-leg-equaliser-against-real-madrid/blt77246db5e800823b |url-status=live }}</ref> in which he managed to score in the same round for the third consecutive year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/10075501-kevin-de-bruyne-hyped-by-man-city-fans-for-clutch-play-after-ucl-draw-vs-real-madrid |title=Kevin De Bruyne Hyped by Man City Fans for Clutch Play After UCL Draw vs. Real Madrid |publisher=Bleacher Report |date=9 May 2023 |access-date=18 July 2023 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718181737/https://bleacherreport.com/articles/10075501-kevin-de-bruyne-hyped-by-man-city-fans-for-clutch-play-after-ucl-draw-vs-real-madrid |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 10 June, he played only 36 minutes in his second [[2023 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]], as he suffered a hamstring injury and was replaced by [[Phil Foden]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Dawson |first=Rob |date=10 June 2023 |title=Man City's Kevin De Bruyne forced off with injury in 1st half of Champions League final |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37832217/manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-injury-champions-league-final |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=10 June 2023}}</ref> However, Manchester City eventually won 1–0 against [[Inter Milan]], which completed their [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.sky.com/story/manchester-city-win-treble-with-1-0-champions-league-final-victory-over-inter-12900070 |title=A treble! Manchester City win Champions League, FA Cup and Premier League |publisher=Sky News |date=11 June 2023 |access-date=18 July 2023 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718173446/https://news.sky.com/story/manchester-city-win-treble-with-1-0-champions-league-final-victory-over-inter-12900070 |url-status=live}}</ref>

After the season, De Bruyne was nominated for [[UEFA Men's Player of the Year Award]] along with [[Lionel Messi]] and Manchester City teammate [[Erling Haaland]].<ref>{{cite web |last= |date=17 August 2023 |title=2022/23 UEFA Men's Player of the Year award nominees announced: Kevin De Bruyne, Erling Haaland, Lionel Messi |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0284-18c1b70cc3e6-ccc3c4cc0186-1000--2022-23-uefa-men-s-player-of-the-year-award-nominees-announc/ |access-date=21 August 2023 |publisher=[[UEFA]] |archive-date=20 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230820001136/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0284-18c1b70cc3e6-ccc3c4cc0186-1000--2022-23-uefa-men-s-player-of-the-year-award-nominees-announc/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

====2023–24 season====
De Bruyne started the [[2023–24 Manchester City F.C. season|2023–24 season]] coming on as a substitute in the [[2023 FA Community Shield]] against Arsenal on 6 August, missing a penalty as the Gunners won the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]] 4–1.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2023/aug/06/arsenal-v-manchester-city-community-shield-live |title=Arsenal 1–1 Man City (4–1 on pens): as it happened |first=Rob |last=Smyth |work=The Guardian |date=6 August 2023 |accessdate=12 August 2023 |archive-date=17 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230817102238/https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2023/aug/06/arsenal-v-manchester-city-community-shield-live |url-status=live |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 11 August, he suffered a reoccurrence of a hamstring injury in the opening league game of the season against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], it was later confirmed he would be out for four to five months.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4772984/2023/08/15/de-bruyne-injury-update-manchester-city/ |title=Kevin De Bruyne injury 'serious', Manchester City midfielder out for 'few months' |first=Mark |last=Critchley |work=The Athletic |date=15 August 2023 |access-date=15 August 2023 |archive-date=15 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815150659/https://theathletic.com/4772984/2023/08/15/de-bruyne-injury-update-manchester-city/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his return from injury on 7 January 2024, providing an assist in a 5–0 win over [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in the [[2023–24 FA Cup|FA Cup]] third round.<ref>{{cite web |first=Gary |last=Rose |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67907682 |title=Kevin de Bruyne: Man City boss Pep Guardiola says 'the people love him' as midfielder returns |work=BBC Sport |date=7 January 2024 |access-date=7 January 2024 |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107212609/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67907682 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 13 January, he came off the bench, scoring his first goal of the season and assisting another in a 3–2 comeback away victory over Newcastle United.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/67927667 |title=Newcastle United 2–3 Manchester City |work=BBC Sport |date=13 January 2024 |access-date=14 January 2024 |archive-date=13 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240113193959/https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/67927667 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 6 April 2024, De Bruyne scored his 100th goal for Manchester City in a 4–2 win at Crystal Palace.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68697135|title=Crystal Palace 2–4 Man City: Kevin de Bruyne shines as defending champions maintain title challenge|date=6 April 2024|access-date=8 April 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 17 April, he scored a goal in a 1–1 draw against Real Madrid in the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League quarter-final]] second leg, levelling the aggregate score at 4–4; however, his club lost 4–3 in the penalty shootout.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68830107 |title=Manchester City 1–1 Real Madrid (agg 4–4, 3–4 on pens): Spaniards through after shootout |work=BBC Sport |date=17 April 2024 }}</ref> On 19 May, he achieved his 6th [[2023–24 Premier League|Premier League]] title with the club on the final matchday of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cjmmlgr4g0eo |title='One of the most special' titles for De Bruyne |work=BBC Sport |date=19 May 2024 }}</ref>

