| quoted = 1
}}

On 4 April 2025, De Bruyne announced that he would leave Manchester City upon the expiration of his contract at the end of the [[2024–25 Manchester City F.C. season|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cj3x0jpmgv4o |title=De Bruyne to leave Manchester City at end of season |website=BBC Sport |date=4 April 2025 |access-date=4 April 2025}}</ref> On 17 May, De Bruyne had the opportunity to win his 20th and final trophy with Manchester City, but the club's campaign in the FA Cup ended in defeat in the [[2025 FA Cup final|final]], which City lost 1–0 to [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite web |date=17 May 2023 |title=Afscheid in mineur voor De Bruyne: vroege goal van Palace nekt City, dat Belg geen laatste FA Cup kan schenken |trans-title=Minor farewell for De Bruyne: early goal from Palace defeats City, who cannot give the Belgian a final FA Cup |url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/buitenland/eng/the-emirates-fa-cup/2024-2025/finale/01/crystal-palace-manchester-city-afscheid-in-mineur-voor-de-bruyne-vroege-goal-van-palace-nekt-city-dat-belg-geen-laatste-fa-cup-kan-schenken~1729870929582/ |access-date= |work=[[Sporza]] |language=nl}}</ref> In his final home game three days later, "King Kev" was extensively honored, including with a temporary mural.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 May 2025 |title=Niemand houdt het droog bij eerbetoon voor De Bruyne, die ook afscheid neemt met de lach: "Dit is onbeschrijfelijk" |trans-title=No one can hold back tears at the tribute to De Bruyne, who also says goodbye with a smile: "This is indescribable" |url=https://sporza.be/nl/2025/05/20/niemand-houdt-het-droog-bij-eerbetoon-voor-de-bruyne-die-ook-afscheid-neemt-met-de-lach-dit-is-onbeschrijfelijk~1747768040770/ |access-date= |work=[[Sporza]] |language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=14 May 2025 |title=King Kev: Iconic KDB mural unveiled |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/king-kev-kevin-de-bruyne-mural-installed-63882836 |website=mancity.com |language=}}</ref>

With 16 major trophies, the 33-year-old De Bruyne left Manchester City as one of the most decorated players in the club's history.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 January 2025 |title=Kevin De Bruyne made his 400th City appearance in the 4-1 win over West Ham. |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/kevin-de-bruyne-400-city-appearances-63871500|website=mancity.com |language=}}</ref>

===Napoli===
On 12 June 2025, [[Serie A]] club [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]] announced the signing of De Bruyne on a free transfer.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lombardi |first=Giuseppe |date=12 June 2025 |title=SSCN {{!}} Ufficiale l'ingaggio di De Bruyne |url=https://sscnapoli.it/sscn-ufficiale-lingaggio-di-de-bruyne/ |access-date=13 June 2025 |publisher=[[SSC Napoli]] |language=it|trans-title=SSCN {{!}} De Bruyne signing official}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Smith |first=Emma |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cx2q3v2re7go |title=De Bruyne completes Napoli move after Man City exit |website=BBC Sport |date=12 June 2025 |access-date=12 June 2025}}</ref> On 23 August, he netted his first goal on his league debut in a 2–0 away win over [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Kearns |first=Sean |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c4gmj0ze0xjt |title=Sassuolo 0–2 Napoli |publisher=BBC Sport |date=23 August 2025 |access-date=29 March 2026}}</ref> On 13 September, he scored again during a 3–1 away win over [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fiorentina VS Napoli |url=https://www.legaseriea.it/en/match/2025-26-fiorentina-napoli-serie-a-matchday-3 |access-date=13 September 2025 |website=www.legaseriea.it}}</ref> A month later, on 25 October, he sustained a hamstring injury after scoring a penalty in a 3–1 win over Inter Milan.<ref>{{cite web |last=Botcherby |first=Elizabeth |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cn09qyv027qo |title=De Bruyne has surgery after penalty thigh injury |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 October 2025 |access-date=29 March 2026}}</ref> He made his return to action as a substitute in a 2–1 victory over [[Torino FC|Torino]] on 6 March 2026.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/napoli-v-torino-line-ups-184300966.html |title=Napoli close gap to Milan, De Bruyne and Anguissa return |publisher=Yahoo! Sports |date=6 March 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Vincent Kompany Simon Mignolet Kevin De Bruyne vs USA.jpg|thumb|De Bruyne (right) lining up for Belgium in 2013, alongside [[Vincent Kompany]] and [[Simon Mignolet]]]]
De Bruyne represented [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] at [[Belgium national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[Belgium national under-19 football team|under-19]], and [[Belgium national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels. He made his [[Belgium national football team|senior team]] debut on 11 August 2010 in an [[Exhibition game|international friendly match]] against [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in [[Turku]]; the game ended in a 1–0 loss for Belgium.<ref>{{Cite news|title=13 fun facts about Kevin De Bruyne|url=https://www.goal.com/en-cm/lists/13-fun-facts-about-kevin-de-bruyne/blt02c4e080a8fed912|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=22 February 2023|access-date=12 July 2024}}</ref> Before making his full debut for Belgium's senior side, De Bruyne was eligible to play for [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]], his mother's birthplace.<ref name="fightforchance">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/kevin-de-bruyne-interview-ill-fight-for-chance-at-chelsea-8845258.html|title=Kevin De Bruyne interview: I'll fight for chance at Chelsea...|newspaper=The Independent|access-date=5 June 2015|archive-date=25 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925215906/http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/kevin-de-bruyne-interview-ill-fight-for-chance-at-chelsea-8845258.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

De Bruyne became a regular member of Belgium's team during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification - UEFA Group A|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]] campaign, where he scored four goals as the Red Devils qualified for their first major tournament in 12 years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kevin De Bruyne|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/players/player=358120/news.html|publisher=[[FIFA]]|access-date=22 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140622045843/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/players/player=358120/news.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=22 June 2014}}</ref>

===2014–2016: First World Cup and Euro appearances===
[[File:Kevin De Bruyne - World Cup 2014.png|thumb|De Bruyne playing for Belgium against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]]]]
On 13 May 2014, De Bruyne was named in Belgium's squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Adnan Januzaj included in Belgium's World Cup squad|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27395150|access-date=15 May 2014|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=BBC|date=13 May 2014|archive-date=26 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126180206/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27395150|url-status=live}}</ref> In their first game of the tournament, against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] in [[Belo Horizonte]], De Bruyne assisted [[Marouane Fellaini]]'s equaliser<ref>{{cite news|first=Saj|last=Chowdhury|title=Belgium 2–1 Algeria|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25285127|access-date=17 June 2014|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=17 June 2014|archive-date=26 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126180207/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25285127|url-status=live}}</ref> and was named [[man of the match]] by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=255931/match=300186479/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140620111617/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=255931/match=300186479/|url-status=dead|archive-date=20 June 2014|title=Belgium 2–1 Algeria|access-date=22 June 2014|publisher=FIFA}}</ref> In the [[2014 FIFA World Cup round of 16|round of 16]], De Bruyne scored Belgium's opening goal in the third minute of [[Overtime (association football)|extra time]] as they defeated the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] 2–1.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/27990605|title=Belgium 2–1 USA|date=1 July 2014|access-date=2 July 2014|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|archive-date=16 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151216143105/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/27990605|url-status=live}}</ref> They were subsequently eliminated from the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] after losing 1–0 to [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Quarter-finals|quarter-finals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28069209|title=Argentina 1 Belgium 0|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=5 July 2014|access-date=28 January 2024|archive-date=19 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119142253/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28069209|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 10 October 2014, De Bruyne scored twice in a 6–0 rout of [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying]], equalling the team's record victory in a European qualifier set in 1986.<ref>{{cite news|first=Derek|last=Brookman|title=Belgium equal record tally against Andorra|url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/news/0253-0d7f6871bfee-b577ff83af3a-1000--belgium-equal-record-tally-against-andorra/|access-date=30 August 2015|publisher=UEFA|date=10 October 2014|archive-date=12 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151012050417/http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/qualifiers/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2013852/postmatch/report/index.html#belgium+equal+record+tally|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/2013852--belgium-vs-andorra/|title=UEFA EURO 2016 {{!}} History|publisher=UEFA|date=10 October 2014|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=26 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626195252/http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2013852/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref> On 3 September 2015, De Bruyne scored in a 3–1 win over [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/2013973--belgium-vs-bosnia-and-herzegovina/ |title=UEFA EURO 2016 {{!}} History |publisher=UEFA |date=3 September 2015 |access-date=26 June 2018 |archive-date=19 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190519204240/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2013973/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 October 2015, De Bruyne scored in a 4–1 victory against [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]], which secured Belgium's place at the [[UEFA Euro 2016]] finals.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/33543987|title=Andorra 1–4 Belgium|date=10 October 2015|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=22 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151122070311/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/33543987|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/2014042--andorra-vs-belgium/|title=UEFA EURO 2016 {{!}} History|publisher=UEFA|date=10 October 2015|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321175829/http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2014042/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Three days later, he scored in a 3–1 win over [[Israel national football team|Israel]], securing Belgium [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group B|top-spot in the group]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/2014068--belgium-vs-israel/|title=UEFA EURO 2016 {{!}} History|publisher=UEFA|date=13 October 2015|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=12 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190512193106/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2016/matches/round=2000446/match=2014068/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 31 May 2016, De Bruyne was selected for Belgium's final 23-man [[UEFA Euro 2016 squads#Belgium|squad]] for [[UEFA Euro 2016]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/29908/10300579/marc-wilmots-unveils-belgium-squad-for-euro-2016 |title=Marc Wilmots unveils Belgium squad for Euro 2016 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=31 May 2016 }}</ref> On 18 June 2016, De Bruyne was praised for his performance in Belgium's 3–0 win over the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://squawka.com/en/news/player-ratings-belgium-3-0-republic-of-ireland-de-bruyne-conducts-dominant-win-for-red-devils/700929|title=Player ratings: Belgium 3–0 Republic of Ireland {{!}} De Bruyne conducts dominant win for Red Devils|website=Squawka Football News|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=26 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626192327/https://squawka.com/en/news/player-ratings-belgium-3-0-republic-of-ireland-de-bruyne-conducts-dominant-win-for-red-devils/700929|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 26 June 2016, De Bruyne was voted [[BBC Sport|BBC]] ''Man of the Match'' for his performance in a 4–0 win over [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] in the [[UEFA Euro 2016#Round of 16|round of 16]], where he provided two assists.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36569531|title=Hungary 0–4 Belgium|date=26 June 2016|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=11 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711010309/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36569531|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2016–2018: 2018 World Cup===
[[File:Kevin De Bruyne celebrating Belgium's 2–1 win over Brazil.jpg|thumb|De Bruyne celebrating Belgium's 2–1 win over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]
De Bruyne was selected for Belgium's final 23-man [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#Belgium|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/belgiums-2018-world-cup-squad-who-joins-hazard-lukaku-23-man/1o481lo2g3q5511q2qts8u7xoy|title=Belgium's 2018 World Cup squad: Who joins Hazard & Lukaku in the 23-man squad?|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=19 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190719155714/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/belgiums-2018-world-cup-squad-who-joins-hazard-lukaku-23-man/1o481lo2g3q5511q2qts8u7xoy|url-status=live}}</ref> On 18 June, in the opening game against debutants [[Panama national football team|Panama]], De Bruyne provided an assist for [[Romelu Lukaku]] in an eventual 3–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331539/#match-summary|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612141627/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331539/#match-summary|url-status=dead|archive-date=12 June 2018|title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia {{!}} Matches {{!}} Belgium vs. Panama|publisher=FIFA|access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44434275|title=World Cup 2018: Belgium beat debutants Panama 3–0 in Sochi|date=18 June 2018|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|access-date=26 June 2018|archive-date=14 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814015734/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44434275|url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 July, he scored the second goal of the match in a 2–1 [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Brazil vs Belgium|quarter-final]] victory over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] and was named the man of the match.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Wilson |first=Jonathan |date=6 July 2018 |title=Brazil knocked out of World Cup by Kevin De Bruyne and brilliant Belgium |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jul/06/brazil-belgium-world-cup-quarter-final-match-report |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108053553/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jul/06/brazil-belgium-world-cup-quarter-final-match-report |archive-date=8 January 2020 |access-date=29 March 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> In the semi-finals, Belgium were defeated 1–0 by eventual champions [[France national football team|France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44692297 |title=France 1–0 Belgium |work=BBC Sport |first=Shamoon |last=Hafez |date=10 June 2018 |access-date=10 June 2018 |archive-date=5 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905074231/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44692297 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 14 July, Belgium defeated [[England national football team|England]] 2–0 in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup#Third place play-off|third-place play-off]].<ref>{{cite news |title=World Cup 2018: England finish fourth after Belgium defeat |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44748604 |access-date=14 July 2018|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|archive-date=19 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190519105251/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44748604 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===2018–2022: Euro 2020 and 2022 World Cup===
[[File:Kevin De Bruyne WC2022.jpg|thumb|De Bruyne playing for Belgium against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]
On 17 June 2021, De Bruyne scored his first and the winning goal in Belgium's second match of [[UEFA Euro 2020]], a 2–1 victory over [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Marsh |first=Charlotte |title=Denmark 1–2 Belgium: Kevin De Bruyne inspires Red Devils to victory as they reach Euro 2020 last 16 |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/19692/12335073/denmark-1-2-belgium-kevin-de-bruyne-inspires-red-devils-to-victory-as-they-reach-last-16 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=17 June 2021 |access-date=6 August 2021 |archive-date=31 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210731111424/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/19692/12335073/denmark-1-2-belgium-kevin-de-bruyne-inspires-red-devils-to-victory-as-they-reach-last-16 |url-status=live }}</ref> having earlier in the game assisted the team's first goal.<ref>{{cite web |last=Glendenning |first=Barry |title=Denmark 1–2 Belgium: Euro 2020 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/jun/17/denmark-v-belgium-euro-2020-live |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=17 June 2021 |access-date=20 June 2021 |archive-date=19 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210619142613/https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/jun/17/denmark-v-belgium-euro-2020-live |url-status=live |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> During the round of 16 clash with [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], De Bruyne suffered an ankle injury from a tackle from behind, by Portugal's [[Joao Palhinha]]. On 2 July Belgium manager [[Roberto Martinez]] said that De Bruyne could recover in time for the quarter-final match, later that day, despite not training all week<ref>{{cite news |last=Braw |first=Joe |title=Belgium give fitness update on Man City star Kevin de Bruyne for Italy Euro 2020 clash |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/de-bruyne-injury-belgium-italy-20952371.amp |date=2 July 2021 |newspaper=[[Manchester Evening News]] |access-date=2 July 2021 |archive-date=12 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210712054406/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/de-bruyne-injury-belgium-italy-20952371.amp |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/29908/12346693/kevin-de-bruyne-and-eden-hazard-last-minute-decisions-for-belgiums-euro-2020-quarter-final-against-italy-says-roberto-martinez|title=Kevin de Bruyne and Eden Hazard last-minute decisions for Belgium's Euro 2020 quarter-final against Italy, says Roberto Martinez|work=Sky Sports |access-date=2 July 2021|archive-date=12 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210712001414/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/29908/12346693/kevin-de-bruyne-and-eden-hazard-last-minute-decisions-for-belgiums-euro-2020-quarter-final-against-italy-says-roberto-martinez|url-status=live}}</ref> and he was later confirmed in the starting line-up.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/belgium-italy-live-stream-euro-2020-b1877068.html |title=Belgium vs Italy Live: Euro 2020 team news, line-ups and more today {{!}} The Independent |website=The Independent |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210702170518/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/belgium-italy-live-stream-euro-2020-b1877068.html |archive-date=2 July 2021}}</ref>

De Bruyne started all three games in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] as Belgium were eliminated in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup Group F|group stage]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Belgium 1–0 Canada|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63644791|access-date=21 March 2023|date=23 November 2022|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|archive-date=21 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230321193329/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63644791|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Belgium 0–2 Morocco|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63692164|access-date=21 March 2023|date=27 November 2022|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|archive-date=21 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230321193329/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63692164|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Croatia 0–0 Belgium|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63739245|access-date=21 March 2023|date=1 December 2022|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|archive-date=26 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226160755/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63739245|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2022–present: Assuming the captaincy===
On 21 March 2023, De Bruyne was announced as Belgium's new [[Captain (association football)|captain]], following the international retirement of [[Eden Hazard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rbfa.be/en/news/kevin-de-bruyne-new-captain-belgian-red-devils|title=Kevin De Bruyne is the new captain of the Belgian Red Devils|website=Royal Belgian Football Association|date=21 March 2023|access-date=21 March 2023|archive-date=21 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230321193330/https://www.rbfa.be/en/news/kevin-de-bruyne-new-captain-belgian-red-devils|url-status=live}}</ref> A week later, he led Belgium to beat [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in a friendly match for the first time since 1954, by scoring a goal and providing two assists in a 3–2 away win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brusselstimes.com/431905/belgium-triumph-in-germany-for-the-first-time-since-1954 |title=Belgium triumph in Germany for the first time since 1954 |work=The Brussels Times |date=29 March 2023 |access-date=18 July 2023 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718173446/https://www.brusselstimes.com/431905/belgium-triumph-in-germany-for-the-first-time-since-1954 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 28 May 2024, he was selected in the Belgian squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=28 May 2024 |title=25 Devils go to EURO 2024 |url=https://www.rbfa.be/en/news/25-devils-go-euro-2024 |publisher=[[Royal Belgian Football Association]] |access-date=28 May 2024}}</ref> A few days later, on 5 June, he earned his 100th international cap, in which he also scored a goal, in a 2–0 friendly victory over [[Montenegro national football team|Montenegro]] prior to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |last=Mukherjee |first=Soham |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/100-caps-kevin-de-bruyne-belgium-montenegro-euro-2024-friendly/bltaf8d68312a26b1cb |title=What a way to mark 100 caps! Kevin De Bruyne scores on landmark game as Belgium cruise past Montenegro in Euro 2024 warm-up friendly|website=Goal (website)|date=5 June 2024|access-date=29 March 2026}}</ref>

On 3 September 2025, manager [[Rudi Garcia]] - after previously rotating the captaincy around members of the squad - announced that [[Youri Tielemans]] would be Belgium's new captain, succeeding De Bruyne in the role.<ref>{{Cite news |date=3 September 2025 |title=Tielemans named as new Belgium captain |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/tielemans-named-new-belgium-captain-2025-09-03/ |access-date=3 September 2025 |work=Reuters |language=en}}</ref>

==Player profile==
===Style of play===
He primarily plays as an [[attacking midfielder|attacking]] or [[central midfielder]], although he has also been used as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]], [[second striker]], and even in a [[Deep-lying playmaker|deeper creative midfield]] position. On occasion, he has been deployed with a [[box-to-box]] role or [[false 9]]. Media and analysts frequently describe him as one of the best [[advanced playmaker]]s in the modern era due to his technique, skill, athleticism, work-rate off the ball, vision, [[Cross (association football)|crossing]] accuracy, wide range of passing, and powerful long-range shooting ability with either foot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.squawka.com/news/do-manchester-city-need-kevin-de-bruyne-this-summer/395150|title=Do Manchester City need Kevin De Bruyne this summer?|publisher=Squawka|date=11 June 2015|access-date=16 November 2017|first=Daniel|last=Anwar|archive-date=6 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706131900/http://www.squawka.com/news/do-manchester-city-need-kevin-de-bruyne-this-summer/395150|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/manchester-city/11833859/Kevin-De-Bruyne-completes-54m-Man-City-transfer.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/manchester-city/11833859/Kevin-De-Bruyne-completes-54m-Man-City-transfer.html |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=Kevin De Bruyne completes £54m Man City transfer|work=The Daily Telegraph|first1=Mark |last1=Ogden|first2=Mike |last2=Whalley|date=30 August 2015|access-date=13 July 2016}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/686309 |title=De Bruyne the drive behind Man City success |publisher=Premier League |first=Adrian |last=Clarke |date=11 May 2018 |access-date=8 December 2018 |archive-date=9 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181209124305/https://www.premierleague.com/news/686309 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-perfect-complete-guardiola-conte-reaction-a7976051.html |title=Pep Guardiola and Antonio Conte laud Kevin De Bruyne for being the perfect 'complete' player after masterclass |newspaper=The Independent |first=Miguel |last=Delaney |date=30 September 2017 |access-date=8 December 2018 |archive-date=30 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330183241/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-perfect-complete-guardiola-conte-reaction-a7976051.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tsn.ca/de-bruyne-s-versatility-a-key-for-belgium-1.1134678 |title=De Bruyne's versatility a key for Belgium |publisher=TSN |date=9 July 2018 |access-date=17 December 2018 |archive-date=17 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217202337/https://www.tsn.ca/de-bruyne-s-versatility-a-key-for-belgium-1.1134678 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/barclays-premier-league/23/blog/post/2935772/premier-league-disappointing-lack-of-deep-lying-playmakers |title=Disappointing lack of deep-lying playmakers in the Premier League |publisher=ESPN FC |last1=Cox |first1=Michael |date=23 August 2016 |access-date=24 August 2019 |archive-date=24 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190824140647/https://www.espn.com/soccer/barclays-premier-league/23/blog/post/2935772/premier-league-disappointing-lack-of-deep-lying-playmakers |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-de-bruyne-palace-16991871 |title=The attacking dynamic that Kevin De Bruyne will restore for Pep Guardiola |work=The Manchester Evening News |last1=Williams |first1=Josh |date=18 October 2019 |access-date=6 November 2019 |archive-date=6 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191106140507/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-de-bruyne-palace-16991871 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/us/features/manchester-city-how-the-false-nine-became-pep-guardiolas-plan-a |title=Manchester City: How the false nine became Pep Guardiola's Plan A |publisher=fourfourtwo.com |last=Jolly |first=Richard |date=5 March 2021 |access-date=29 April 2021 |archive-date=29 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210429034811/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/us/features/manchester-city-how-the-false-nine-became-pep-guardiolas-plan-a |url-status=live}}</ref>

Although he is not blessed with significant physical strength, pace, or ability in the air,<ref name="Generazione di Fenomeni">{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/it/news/3785/generazione-di-fenomeni/2011/11/16/2756464/generazione-di-fenomeni-kevin-de-bruyne-il-gioiello-del-genk-che- |title=Generazione di Fenomeni – Kevin De Bruyne, il gioiello del Genk che il Chelsea sta corteggiando da anni... |work=Goal (website) |language=it |first=Simone |last=Gambino |date=16 November 2011 |access-date=17 December 2018 |archive-date=18 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218010617/https://www.goal.com/it/news/3785/generazione-di-fenomeni/2011/11/16/2756464/generazione-di-fenomeni-kevin-de-bruyne-il-gioiello-del-genk-che- |url-status=live|trans-title=Generation of Phenoms – Kevin De Bruyne, the Genk jewel that Chelsea has been courting for years...}}</ref> he is a quick and elegant player on the ball with good [[Dribbling (association football)|dribbling]] skills, while his positional sense, tactical intelligence, movement, direct style of play and ability to run at defences when in possession also enable him to take advantage of spaces in the opposition's defence and subsequently create chances and goalscoring opportunities for himself or his team-mates, making him a dangerous offensive threat on counter-attacks.<ref name="Generazione di Fenomeni" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/premier-league/2017-2018/soccer-de-bruyne-performance-leaves-guardiola-speechless_sto6446741/story.shtml |title=Kevin De Bruyne performance leaves Pep Guardiola speechless |publisher=Eurosport |date=16 December 2017 |access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/09/22/kevin-de-bruyne-is-one-of-best-players-ive-worked-with-says-pep/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/09/22/kevin-de-bruyne-is-one-of-best-players-ive-worked-with-says-pep/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Kevin De Bruyne 'is one of best players I've worked with' says Pep Guardiola – but what makes him so special? |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |first=JJ |last=Bull |date=22 September 2016 |access-date=8 December 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://vivoperlei.calciomercato.com/articolo/dopo-messi-e-cr7-a-chi-il-pallone-doro?referral=vxl_box_mobile |title=Dopo Messi e Cr7 a chi il pallone d'Oro? |publisher=Calciomercato |language=it |first=Ammiraglio |last=Byrd |date=4 October 2016 |access-date=17 December 2018 |archive-date=17 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217202343/https://vivoperlei.calciomercato.com/articolo/dopo-messi-e-cr7-a-chi-il-pallone-doro?referral=vxl_box_mobile |url-status=live|trans-title=After Messi and CR7, who gets the Ballon d'Oro?}}</ref> In addition to his creative abilities,<ref name="Generazione di Fenomeni" /> he is also capable of scoring goals by making late runs off the ball from behind into the penalty area<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/it/news/14802/uefacom/2016/06/08/24370292/pogba-de-bruyne-e-i-migliori-centrocampisti-di-uefa-euro |title=Pogba, De Bruyne e i migliori centrocampisti di UEFA EURO 2016 |work=Goal (website) |language=it |date=8 June 2016 |access-date=17 December 2018 |archive-date=18 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218010602/https://www.goal.com/it/news/14802/uefacom/2016/06/08/24370292/pogba-de-bruyne-e-i-migliori-centrocampisti-di-uefa-euro |url-status=live}}</ref> and is an accurate [[Set piece (football)|set-piece]] taker.<ref name="Generazione di Fenomeni" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.sports.yahoo.com/news/goals-assists-set-pieces-stats-172816108.html |title=Goals, assists, set-pieces – The stats that show De Bruyne is almost irreplaceable for City |publisher=Yahoo |date=15 August 2018 |access-date=17 December 2018 |archive-date=20 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181020224100/https://uk.sports.yahoo.com/news/goals-assists-set-pieces-stats-172816108.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Reception===
At his peak, De Bruyne was widely regarded as one of the best players in the world,<ref>{{cite news|last=Brown|first=Luke|date=9 November 2017|title=Kevin de Bruyne can become as good as Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo, says Roberto Martinez|newspaper=The Independent|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/kevin-de-bruyne-as-good-lionel-messi-cristiano-ronaldo-manchester-city-real-madrid-barcelona-a8045706.html|access-date=16 November 2017|archive-date=30 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330181732/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/kevin-de-bruyne-as-good-lionel-messi-cristiano-ronaldo-manchester-city-real-madrid-barcelona-a8045706.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pep Guardiola calls Kevin De Bruyne "the best player in Europe bar one"|url=http://www.squawka.com/news/pep-guardiola-calls-kevin-de-bruyne-the-best-player-in-europe-bar-one/999940|last=Siregar|first=Cady|date=16 October 2017|publisher=Squawka|access-date=16 November 2017|archive-date=25 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180525115546/http://www.squawka.com/news/pep-guardiola-calls-kevin-de-bruyne-the-best-player-in-europe-bar-one/999940|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kevin De Bruyne best player in Premier League at the moment – Eden Hazard|url=http://www.espnfc.com/manchester-city/story/3264836/kevin-de-bruyne-best-player-in-the-premier-league-at-the-moment-eden-hazard|last=Holyman|first=Ian|date=10 November 2017|website=ESPN FC|access-date=16 November 2017|archive-date=7 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307072946/http://www.espnfc.com/manchester-city/story/3264836/kevin-de-bruyne-best-player-in-the-premier-league-at-the-moment-eden-hazard|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Hughes praises 'best player' in league De Bruyne|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41623610|date=14 October 2017|website=BBC Sport|access-date=16 November 2017|archive-date=15 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615003846/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41623610|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bayern Munich boss Heynckes: "I would give De Bruyne the shirt off my back"|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/jupp-heynckes-would-give-kevin-de-bruyne-shirt-off-my-back/2eqyxx2j3vqi1dt7leiauui4j|last=McGee|first=Nicholas|date=15 January 2018|website=Goal (website)|access-date=8 July 2018|archive-date=15 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190615080242/https://www.goal.com/en/news/jupp-heynckes-would-give-kevin-de-bruyne-shirt-off-my-back/2eqyxx2j3vqi1dt7leiauui4j|url-status=live}}</ref> and he has often been described as a "complete" footballer.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pep Guardiola and Antonio Conte laud Kevin De Bruyne for being the perfect 'complete' player after masterclass|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-perfect-complete-guardiola-conte-reaction-a7976051.html|last=Delaney|first=Miguel|date=30 September 2017|work=The Independent|access-date=8 July 2018|archive-date=30 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330183241/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-perfect-complete-guardiola-conte-reaction-a7976051.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Where would Manchester City be without Kevin De Bruyne, the most complete player in the Premier League?|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-goals-highlights-most-complete-player-premier-league-a7976031.html|last=Pitt-Brooke|first=Jack|date=30 September 2017|work=The Independent|access-date=7 July 2018|archive-date=30 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330154642/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/chelsea-vs-manchester-city-kevin-de-bruyne-goals-highlights-most-complete-player-premier-league-a7976031.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=FourFourTwo's 100 Best Football Players in the World 2017: No.5, Kevin De Bruyne|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/fourfourtwos-100-best-football-players-world-2017-no5-kevin-de-bruyne#s5xCu64wy6YVu6Yu.99|date=15 December 2017|work=Talksport|access-date=16 December 2019|quote=The world's most complete midfielder is dropping jaws with his defence-splitting brilliance – and setting himself on the path to superstardom|archive-date=22 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200622063527/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/fourfourtwos-100-best-football-players-world-2017-no5-kevin-de-bruyne#s5xCu64wy6YVu6Yu.99|url-status=live}}</ref> A number of sources have described him as one of the Premier League's best ever players.<ref name=":6" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=14 October 2025 |title=The best Premier League 11 of all time |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/the-best-premier-league-11-of-all-time-38986726 |access-date=14 October 2025 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=14 August 2025 |title=Greatest Premier League XI of all time |url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/feature/greatest-premier-league-xi-of-all-time_579149.html |access-date=14 October 2025 |website=Sports Mole}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last1=Campbell |first1=Jordan |last2=Carey |first2=Mark |date=18 September 2025 |title=Kevin De Bruyne has a chance to remind Man City why he is impossible to replace |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6636817/2025/09/18/kevin-de-bruyne-napoli-man-city/ |access-date=14 October 2025 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

De Bruyne was ranked the fourth-best footballer in the world by ''[[The Guardian]]'' in 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2017/dec/19/the-100-best-footballers-in-the-world-2017-interactive|title=The 100 best footballers in the world 2017|date=19 December 2017|work=[[The Guardian]]|access-date=24 December 2017|archive-date=4 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304152456/https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2017/dec/19/the-100-best-footballers-in-the-world-2017-interactive|url-status=live}}</ref> and the twelfth-best in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=The 100 best male footballers in the world 2019 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/global/ng-interactive/2019/dec/17/the-100-best-male-footballers-in-the-world-2019 |website=The Guardian |date=20 December 2019 |access-date=28 June 2020 |archive-date=28 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230128005228/https://www.theguardian.com/global/ng-interactive/2019/dec/17/the-100-best-male-footballers-in-the-world-2019 |url-status=live |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> In 2020, his Manchester City manager [[Pep Guardiola]] described him as the best midfielder in the world.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12068342/pep-guardiola-hails-kevin-de-bruyne-as-best-midfielder-in-the-world |title=Pep Guardiola hails Kevin De Bruyne as best midfielder in the world |work=Sky Sports |date=10 September 2020 |access-date=12 September 2021 |archive-date=12 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210912142229/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12068342/pep-guardiola-hails-kevin-de-bruyne-as-best-midfielder-in-the-world |url-status=live }}</ref> As City chased [[The Treble]] in the 2022{{ndash}}23 season with De Bruyne playing a leading role, [[Jamie Redknapp]] said that De Bruyne was the best Premier League midfielder he had seen, ranking him above the likes of [[Steven Gerrard]] and [[Frank Lampard]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kevin De Bruyne is world's best midfielder and Man City have treble in their own hands, says Jamie Redknapp |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/18932/12868807/kevin-de-bruyne-is-worlds-best-midfielder-and-man-city-have-treble-in-their-own-hands-says-jamie-redknapp |date=29 April 2023 |location=United Kingdom |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230430102439/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/18932/12868807/kevin-de-bruyne-is-worlds-best-midfielder-and-man-city-have-treble-in-their-own-hands-says-jamie-redknapp |archive-date=30 April 2023 |last=Redknapp |first=Jamie |work=Sky Sports}}</ref>

==Personal life==
[[File:Kevin De Bruyne at Samsung.jpg|thumb|upright|De Bruyne in 2012]]

===Family and relationships===
De Bruyne's mother is Belgian.<ref name="Terreur">{{cite news |last=Terreur |first=Kristof |date=20 October 2017 |title=Kevin De Bruyne: the stubborn boy who developed into a world beater |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/20/kevin-de-bruyne-stubborn--world-beater |access-date=8 September 2018 |archive-date=20 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171020160741/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/20/kevin-de-bruyne-stubborn--world-beater |url-status=live|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> She was born in [[Burundi]] and has also lived in the [[Ivory Coast]].{{citation needed|date=April 2026}} She grew up in London, after her [[Flanders|Flemish]] parents moved to England for work reasons. Only when she met Kevin's father, Herwig, did she return to Belgium.<ref name="Terreur"/>

De Bruyne's parents settled in Drongen, a sub-municipality of the city of [[Ghent]], in Flanders, the [[Dutch language|Dutch]]-speaking part of Belgium.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Pep Guardiola to make surprise visit to Belgium on June 2nd – report – City Watch |url=https://www.mcfcwatch.com/2018/03/20/pep-guardiola-to-make-surprise-visit-to-belgium-on-june-2nd-report/ |access-date=10 May 2018 |archive-date=15 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215182807/https://www.mcfcwatch.com/2018/03/20/pep-guardiola-to-make-surprise-visit-to-belgium-on-june-2nd-report/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=29 September 2017 |title=Kevin De Bruyne: een jongen uit Drongen |language=nl-NL |work=Staantribune |url=https://staantribune.nl/een-jongen-uit-drongen-hoe-het-begon-voor-kevin-de-bruyne/ |url-status=dead |access-date=10 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180511013605/https://staantribune.nl/een-jongen-uit-drongen-hoe-het-begon-voor-kevin-de-bruyne/ |archive-date=11 May 2018|trans-title=Kevin De Bruyne: a boy from Drongen}}</ref> Aside from Dutch, his mother tongue, De Bruyne also speaks English, French and German.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://premierskillsenglish.britishcouncil.org/players/player-week/kevin-de-bruyne|title=Kevin De Bruyne|website=premierskillsenglish.britishcouncil.org|date=7 May 2017|access-date=10 May 2018|archive-date=19 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190719160900/https://premierskillsenglish.britishcouncil.org/players/player-week/kevin-de-bruyne|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I3z_4jZR-ek|title=Kevin de Bruyne im DAZN Interview vor Schalke vs Manchester City|publisher=DAZN_DE on Youtube|date=20 February 2019|access-date=29 December 2019|archive-date=27 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200827163900/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I3z_4jZR-ek|url-status=live}}</ref>

As a child, De Bruyne and his parents regularly visited his grandparents in London. At the time of his move to Chelsea in 2012, De Bruyne stated: "We used to go every year at Christmas and during school holidays. It's my second home."<ref>{{cite web |date=31 January 2012 |title=De Bruyne komt beetje thuis in Londen |trans-title=De Bruyne comes home to London a bit |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dp3lig4f |website=[[Het Nieuwsblad]] |language=nl |access-date=4 September 2023 |archive-date=5 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230405121335/https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dp3lig4f |url-status=live}}</ref>

De Bruyne has been in a relationship with Michèle Lacroix since 2014.<ref>{{cite web |last=Newman |first=Benjamin |url=http://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/michele-lacroix-new-blonde-girlfriend-of-chelseas-de-bruyne-has-posted-pictures-of-the-couple-on-facebook/ |title=Michèle Lacroix, new blonde girlfriend of Chelsea's De Bruyne, has posted pictures of the couple on Facebook |work=101 Great Goals |date=3 January 2014 |access-date=22 March 2015 |archive-date=2 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402102410/http://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/michele-lacroix-new-blonde-girlfriend-of-chelseas-de-bruyne-has-posted-pictures-of-the-couple-on-facebook/ |url-status=dead}}</ref> The couple married in June 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://futballnews.com/kevin-de-bruyne-celebrates-his-wife-michele/|title=Kevin De Bruyne Celebrates His Wife Michèle|website=futballnews.com|date=27 June 2020|access-date=30 July 2020|archive-date=27 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200827163848/https://futballnews.com/kevin-de-bruyne-celebrates-his-wife-michele/|url-status=live}}</ref> and have three children together.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://futballnews.com/kevin-de-bruyne-and-his-wife-michele-lacroix-introduce-their-newborn-baby-suri/ |title=Kevin De Bruyne and his wife Michele Lacroix introduce their newborn baby Suri |website=futballnews.com |date=6 September 2020 |access-date=17 October 2020 |archive-date=1 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221001142301/https://futballnews.com/kevin-de-bruyne-and-his-wife-michele-lacroix-introduce-their-newborn-baby-suri/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

De Bruyne's autobiography, titled ''Keep It Simple'', was published by Borgerhoff & Lamberigts in October 2014,<ref name=northcroft>{{cite news |first=Jonathan |last=Northcroft |title=City Whizzkid |newspaper=[[The Sunday Times]] |date=25 October 2015}}</ref> following an incident between De Bruyne and his compatriot, footballer [[Thibaut Courtois]], in which De Bruyne's then-girlfriend left him for Courtois. De Bruyne wrote in his autobiography, "Although I still cannot believe what Courtois has done, we continue to work together professionally."<ref>{{cite web|title='In one night, Thibaut gave me what I missed with Kevin for years'. Truth behind 'hatred' between De Bruyne and Courtois|url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/2021-04-30-in-one-night-thibaut-gave-me-what-i-missed-with-kevin-for-years-truth-behind-hatred-betwe/|access-date=20 February 2022|website=Tribuna.com|date=30 April 2021|archive-date=20 February 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220220175342/https://tribuna.com/en/news/2021-04-30-in-one-night-thibaut-gave-me-what-i-missed-with-kevin-for-years-truth-behind-hatred-betwe/|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Philanthropy===
De Bruyne was an ambassador for the 2014 [[Special Olympics]], which took place in [[Antwerp]], and was involved in a controversial advertisement campaign via his personal [[Instagram]] account. Employing the slogan (in Dutch): "Would you still be my fan if I looked like this?", De Bruyne was depicted resembling a person with [[Down's syndrome]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=De Bruyne offers support to Special Olympics {{!}} Inside UEFA |url=https://www.uefa.com/insideuefa/social-responsibility/news/0219-0e8ca1ed158e-714b6623df09-1000--de-bruyne-offers-support-to-special-olympics/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201018202647/https://www.uefa.com/insideuefa/social-responsibility/news/0219-0e8ca1ed158e-714b6623df09-1000--de-bruyne-offers-support-to-special-olympics/ |archive-date=18 October 2020 |access-date=29 March 2026 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> Since 2016 the [[Kevin De Bruyne Cup]], an international youth football tournament, has been organised in Drongen, Belgium.<ref>{{Cite web |title=KDB Cup |url=https://kdbcup.be/en/kdb-cup/ |access-date=29 March 2026 |website=KDB Cup - Kevin De Bruyne |language=en-GB}}</ref> De Bruyne was chosen by [[UEFA]] as ambassador for 2018. He presented a check worth 100,000 euros to the [[International Committee of the Red Cross]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=De Bruyne schenkt 100.000 euro van UEFA aan het goede doel |trans-title=De Bruyne donates 100,000 euros from UEFA to charity |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20180308_03397149 |access-date=29 March 2026 |website=Het Nieuwsblad}}</ref> In 2019, De Bruyne and [[Romelu Lukaku]] handed out shoes to needy children in regional hospitals for a special campaign 'Kicks for Kids' organised by [[Roc Nation Sports]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Het hart op de juiste plaats: De Bruyne en Lukaku maken kinderen in nood blij met opvallende kerstactie |trans-title=Heart in the right place: De Bruyne and Lukaku make children in need happy with striking Christmas campaign |url=https://www.hln.be/time-out/het-hart-op-de-juiste-plaats-de-bruyne-en-lukaku-maken-kinderen-in-nood-blij-met-opvallende-kerstactie~a4917032/ |access-date=29 March 2026 |website=www.hln.be}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Jones |first=Rory |date=20 March 2023 |title=Trang Chủ QQ88 |url=https://www.qq8827.com/ |access-date=29 March 2023 |website=www.qq8827.com |language=en-GB}}</ref> De Bruyne has also been involved in other charitable initiatives, including the "[[Common Goal (charity)|Common Goal]]" campaign, which encourages professional footballers to donate 1% of their wages to support various global social causes. In addition, he has donated money to support [[cancer research]] and has been involved in charity matches to raise money for various causes.<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 June 2024 |title=13 fun facts about Kevin De Bruyne |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/13-fun-facts-about-kevin-de-bruyne/blt02c4e080a8fed912#cs35b3a2e1b4fc9783 |website=Goal (website) }}</ref>

In 2023, De Bruyne and his wife were named as ‘godparents’ of the [[Ronald McDonald House Charities|Ronald McDonald Children's Fund]], which ensures that parents with hospitalised children will be able to stay nearby.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jones |first=Rory |date=20 March 2023 |title=Kevin De Bruyne lands McDonald's endorsement deal |url=https://www.sportspro.com/news/kevin-de-bruyne-michele-lacroix-mcdonalds-manchester-city-endorsement-deal/ |access-date=29 March 2026 |website=SportsPro |language=en-GB}}</ref>

